<div type="definition">
<p>INVESTIGATE the TRUTH of a SENTENCE:statement.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current standard word for cross-checking and veryfying a statement is cān 參 which refers to the cross-checking of a public statement against the realities it claims to refer to.</p>
<p>2. Yàn 驗 and zhēng 徵 refer to an attempt to find specific good evidence (often historical evidence) for something.</p>
<p>3. Hé 覈 refers to checking out the real facts of a case someone is making.</p>
        </div>
